%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 0}
  m_Name: AnastasiaDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Tartaria.Integration:Tartaria.Integration:AnastasiaDialogueDatabase
  lines:
  - id: 0
    moon: 1
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: This dome. I watched them build it. Ages ago. They sang while they worked.
  - id: 1
    moon: 1
    category: 0
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: The stones remember their shape. You just reminded them.
  - id: 2
    moon: 1
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Your resonance is... different. Brighter than what the Archive expected.
  - id: 3
    moon: 1
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_milo
    text: He's louder than anyone I've heard in centuries. I think I like it.
  - id: 4
    moon: 1
    category: 1
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Careful with the lower strata. That's where the important things sleep.
  - id: 5
    moon: 1
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: At night, it almost looks like it used to.
  - id: 6
    moon: 2
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The Archive looks like this. All light and facets. But colder.
  - id: 7
    moon: 2
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: These crystals amplify Aether the way a bell amplifies silence.
  - id: 8
    moon: 2
    category: 1
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: I've been in a cave of light for so long, I'd forgotten what darkness smells
      like.
  - id: 9
    moon: 2
    category: 3
    triggerContext: tuning_complete
    text: You're better at that than the original tuners were. Don't tell them I
      said so.
  - id: 10
    moon: 2
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_lirael
    text: She sings to the crystals. They sing back. I wonder if she knows she's
      doing it.
  - id: 11
    moon: 2
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: This was the heart of their resonance network. The first antenna.
  - id: 12
    moon: 2
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: If you put your ear very close... no. I suppose you can't hear it.
  - id: 13
    moon: 3
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Wind. I remember wind. It's one of the first things you forget when you
      become light.
  - id: 14
    moon: 3
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The orphan train tracks... those children. They built this route themselves.
  - id: 15
    moon: 3
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Highland architecture is different. Built to bend, not break. Like reeds.
  - id: 16
    moon: 3
    category: 3
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: The turbines used to power the aqueducts. Water and wind, partners.
  - id: 17
    moon: 3
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_thorne
    text: The airship captain carries something heavy. Not cargo.
  - id: 18
    moon: 3
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_npc
    text: Children echoes are the cruelest thing about this world. They don't know
      they're trapped.
  - id: 19
    moon: 3
    category: 1
    triggerContext: weather_storm
    text: Lightning and Aether were twins once. The architects used both.
  - id: 20
    moon: 3
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: I can see four zones from here. Four incomplete worlds. You'll fix them.
  - id: 21
    moon: 4
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: I know this place. Not this specific fort, but this geometry. I grew up
      in one like it.
  - id: 22
    moon: 4
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Star forts weren't military. They were amplifiers. Five points, each resonating
      at a different frequency.
  - id: 23
    moon: 4
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The moat isn't water anymore. It's liquid corruption. Be careful.
  - id: 24
    moon: 4
    category: 4
    triggerContext: climax
    text: They're trying to destroy what they can't corrupt. That's desperation.
  - id: 25
    moon: 4
    category: 1
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: The fort held. Eight hundred years of neglect and it still held.
  - id: 26
    moon: 4
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_korath
    text: He remembers the old world better than I do. But he carries it differently
      -- like a wound that taught him something.
  - id: 27
    moon: 4
    category: 3
    triggerContext: building
    text: Golden ratio alignments were mandatory in royal architecture. Not for beauty
      -- for function.
  - id: 28
    moon: 4
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: A Star Chamber. Where the Archive was accessed. Where I was... stored.
  - id: 29
    moon: 4
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: Watching the horizon from a star fort. Some things transcend timeline.
  - id: 30
    moon: 5
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: A colosseum! Not for fighting -- for resonance performances. The acoustics
      must be extraordinary.
  - id: 31
    moon: 5
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The seating holds five thousand echo imprints. Five thousand people who
      watched something beautiful.
  - id: 32
    moon: 5
    category: 0
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: The stage is alive again. I can hear the ghost of applause.
  - id: 33
    moon: 5
    category: 4
    triggerContext: tuning_complete
    text: Overtones were sacred. The note above the note -- the truth behind the
      truth.
  - id: 34
    moon: 5
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Water doesn't corrupt -- it preserves. What's beneath the surface may be
      more intact than what's above.
  - id: 35
    moon: 5
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_milo
    text: He's trying to sell tickets to an echo audience. I admire the optimism.
  - id: 36
    moon: 5
    category: 1
    triggerContext: combat_end
    text: The corruption in water is different. Slower. Patient. Like venom.
  - id: 37
    moon: 5
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: If I stood here and sang... would you hear me? Or just the light?
  - id: 38
    moon: 5
    category: 3
    triggerContext: building
    text: Amphitheater acoustics require precise curvature. The golden ratio isn't
      just visual.
  - id: 39
    moon: 6
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Books. Real books. With pages that turn. I haven't touched a page in...
  - id: 40
    moon: 6
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The Living Library wasn't just storage. It was an interface to the Archive.
      My Archive.
  - id: 41
    moon: 6
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: I can feel the Archive here. Like pressing your hand against glass and
      feeling warmth on the other side.
  - id: 42
    moon: 6
    category: 1
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The librarians encoded knowledge in rhythm. Read with your ears, not your
      eyes.
  - id: 43
    moon: 6
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_npc
    text: Veritas. Still at the keys. Still playing the piece that was interrupted.
      Still waiting for the ending.
  - id: 44
    moon: 6
    category: 4
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: The Library is remembering. Sections are lighting up that have been dark
      since the Flood.
  - id: 45
    moon: 6
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_lore
    text: That shelf describes my preservation. In clinical terms. As if archiving
      a person is a simple administrative act.
  - id: 46
    moon: 6
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: I used to read by candlelight. Light reading light. There's a joke in there
      but it makes me tired.
  - id: 47
    moon: 6
    category: 3
    triggerContext: building
    text: Library wings should follow Fibonacci sequencing. Each room slightly larger
      than the last.
  - id: 48
    moon: 6
    category: 4
    triggerContext: climax
    text: The Library is breathing. The whole structure is alive again. I can feel
      every page turning.
  - id: 49
    moon: 7
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Clockwork. Gears that mesh and turn. Do you know what I'd give for a single
      moving part?
  - id: 50
    moon: 7
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The Citadel's orrery mapped every celestial body. Tartarian astronomy was
      mechanical prophecy.
  - id: 51
    moon: 7
    category: 1
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: That sound -- metal touching metal, turning with purpose. It's the most
      physical sound in this world.
  - id: 52
    moon: 7
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: This machine predicted the Mud Flood. The architects who read it had four
      hours to prepare. I was archived in three.
  - id: 53
    moon: 7
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_milo
    text: He keeps poking the gears. He's going to lose a finger and somehow monetize
      it.
  - id: 54
    moon: 7
    category: 4
    triggerContext: tuning_complete
    text: Synchronization was the Tartarian word for prayer. Making things move together.
  - id: 55
    moon: 7
    category: 1
    triggerContext: combat_end
    text: Corrupted machines aren't evil. They're in pain. Gears grinding against
      their own design.
  - id: 56
    moon: 7
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: Tick. Tick. Tick. Time moves here. In the Archive, there is no tick. Only...
      duration.
  - id: 57
    moon: 8
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Things grow here. Roots push through stone. Life refusing to yield. I envy
      roots.
  - id: 58
    moon: 8
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Bioluminescence is Aether expressing itself through biology. Even nature
      builds with sacred ratios.
  - id: 59
    moon: 8
    category: 1
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: The vines knew where to go. They were waiting for permission.
  - id: 60
    moon: 8
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: I can't smell them. That's the cruelest part. I can see beauty but I can't...
      participate in it.
  - id: 61
    moon: 8
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_lirael
    text: Lirael touches the bark and the tree glows brighter. She doesn't know she's
      feeding it.
  - id: 62
    moon: 8
    category: 1
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The root network mirrors the ley lines above. Nature copied the architects.
      Or maybe the other way around.
  - id: 63
    moon: 8
    category: 3
    triggerContext: building
    text: Build with the trees, not against them. The strongest structures let life
      grow through them.
  - id: 64
    moon: 8
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: Sunlight passes through me. I'm too transparent even for a shadow.
  - id: 65
    moon: 9
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Aurora. The sky remembering how to sing in color. This is the frequency
      I was preserved in.
  - id: 66
    moon: 9
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The Spire channels solar energy into Aether. Pure conversion. I am the
      same kind of conversion.
  - id: 67
    moon: 9
    category: 4
    triggerContext: tuning_complete
    text: I can feel the aurora tuning like a voice inside my chest. If I had a chest.
  - id: 68
    moon: 9
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: From up here, the ley lines look like veins. The planet has a circulatory
      system and we're teaching it to pulse again.
  - id: 69
    moon: 9
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_thorne
    text: He sees navigation. I see home. Same light, different meaning.
  - id: 70
    moon: 9
    category: 1
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: For a moment, the aurora and I were the same frequency. I couldn't tell
      where I ended and the sky began.
  - id: 71
    moon: 9
    category: 1
    triggerContext: combat_end
    text: Corruption fears light. It's the one thing they can't absorb. That gives
      me hope.
  - id: 72
    moon: 9
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: At night, I'm almost invisible against the aurora. Two kinds of light,
      overlapping.
  - id: 73
    moon: 10
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The Forge heat... I can sense it even though I can't feel warmth. Like
      a memory of temperature.
  - id: 74
    moon: 10
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Sonic hammering. The Tartarian smiths shaped metal with sound, not muscle.
      Each strike a note.
  - id: 75
    moon: 10
    category: 1
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: The anvil's ring -- B flat. The note of transformation. Matter yielding
      to intent.
  - id: 76
    moon: 10
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: This alloy responds to Aether. The smiths sang to their creations. The
      creations listened.
  - id: 77
    moon: 10
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_korath
    text: He's remembering the old forges. The ones that made the tools that built
      the world I lost.
  - id: 78
    moon: 10
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The planet's core is pure frequency. We're building on top of the universe's
      bass note.
  - id: 79
    moon: 10
    category: 3
    triggerContext: building
    text: Forged Tartarian alloy resonates for centuries. These buildings will outlast
      any flood.
  - id: 80
    moon: 10
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: Fire is the only element that creates light. We have that in common.
  - id: 81
    moon: 11
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: Water and Archives have the same function -- preserving what was. But water
      doesn't choose what it keeps.
  - id: 82
    moon: 11
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The Tidal Archive is older than the planetary one. Older than the civilization
      that built me.
  - id: 83
    moon: 11
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: I float through water the way I float through everything. No resistance.
      No... interaction.
  - id: 84
    moon: 11
    category: 4
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: A whole city. Intact. Under the surface. They chose to let the tide take
      them rather than fight it.
  - id: 85
    moon: 11
    category: 1
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The tide writes in light. I can almost read it. Almost.
  - id: 86
    moon: 11
    category: 1
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: The water is clearing. I can see all the way down. All the way to the old
      world.
  - id: 87
    moon: 11
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_lirael
    text: Lirael stands at the waterline. The tide reaches for her and passes through.
      We both know how that feels.
  - id: 88
    moon: 11
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: Tides come and go. Echoes stay. I'm not sure which is lonelier.
  - id: 89
    moon: 12
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: The Observatory mapped the stars that map us. Everything is geometry at
      sufficient distance.
  - id: 90
    moon: 12
    category: 0
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: These lenses were ground to Tartarian precision -- twelve decimal places.
      The stars demanded nothing less.
  - id: 91
    moon: 12
    category: 1
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: I recognize these constellations. They've shifted since I was archived.
      Even the sky moved on without me.
  - id: 92
    moon: 12
    category: 4
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: 432 Hz. The frequency that connects the planet to the cosmos. The frequency
      of home.
  - id: 93
    moon: 12
    category: 2
    triggerContext: companion_npc
    text: The navigator sees patterns I can feel but not name. Mathematics made manifest.
  - id: 94
    moon: 12
    category: 0
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: The planet can see the sky again. And the sky can see us.
  - id: 95
    moon: 12
    category: 3
    triggerContext: building
    text: Observatory construction requires absolute stillness. No vibration. Not
      even from the wind.
  - id: 96
    moon: 12
    category: 5
    triggerContext: idle
    text: I used to wish on stars. Now I'm the same kind of light. I wish on sunrises
      instead.
  - id: 97
    moon: 13
    category: 4
    triggerContext: discovery
    text: All the ley lines. Every one. Connected. I can feel the whole planet. It's...
      awake.
  - id: 98
    moon: 13
    category: 4
    triggerContext: restoration
    text: This is what the Archive preserved us for. This moment. All the silence
      was for this.
  - id: 99
    moon: 13
    category: 1
    triggerContext: pre_climax
    text: Whatever happens next -- the digging, the tuning, the building, the quiet
      afternoons -- it mattered. All of it.
  - id: 100
    moon: 13
    category: 4
    triggerContext: climax
    text: Listen. The world is singing. After eight hundred years of silence. It's
      singing.
  - id: 101
    moon: 13
    category: 5
    triggerContext: post_climax
    text: ...thank you. For bringing it all back. For bringing me back. Almost.
  - id: 102
    moon: 0
    category: 7
    triggerContext: solidification_final
    text: ...I can feel the ground.
  - id: 103
    moon: 0
    category: 5
    triggerContext: post_solidification
    text: Ten seconds. That's more than most people get in a lifetime.
  - id: 104
    moon: 1
    category: 6
    triggerContext: mote_0
    text: You found it. A piece of me I didn't know was missing.
  - id: 105
    moon: 6
    category: 6
    triggerContext: mote_5
    text: That shelf. That exact shelf. That's where my record is stored. My... biography
      in light.
  - id: 106
    moon: 11
    category: 6
    triggerContext: mote_10
    text: ...this was my room. Before. The mote is sitting right where my bed used
      to be.
  - id: 107
    moon: 0
    category: 0
    triggerContext: reserved_dlc_01
    text: 
  - id: 108
    moon: 0
    category: 0
    triggerContext: reserved_dlc_02
    text: 
  - id: 109
    moon: 0
    category: 0
    triggerContext: reserved_dlc_03
    text: 
  - id: 110
    moon: 0
    category: 0
    triggerContext: reserved_dlc_04
    text: 
  - id: 111
    moon: 0
    category: 0
    triggerContext: reserved_dlc_05
    text: 
